-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Refiner Mol Shares Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-23T15:44:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-refiner-mol-shares-move-in-budapest.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index fell 3.1
percent to 16,230.31 by the close in Budapest, the biggest
plunge since November.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , the country’s largest lender slid
4.6 percent to 3,374 forint as concern grew that Greece may
leave the euro as the region’s leaders met in Brussels.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, slumped 4.3
percent to 15,520 forint. Oil fell to the lowest level in almost
seven months after an Energy Department report showed that U.S.
crude supplies rose to a 22-year high.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
